From Scott Raney Subject Re Hypercard for UNIX Ronald Queloz writes Hi netlanders Does anybody know if there is something like Macintosh Hypercard for any UNIX platform There are several products you might If you've got per seat and high end hardware Gain Momentum might be a good It isn't compatible with HyperCard but has a similar architecture and way more functionality I don't have contact information but they were recently purchased by Sybase who shouldn't be too hard to If you're running News on SPARC check out HyperLook It uses Postscript as a scripting language which is good if you need to do lots of display oriented scripting but not so good for non It was last I You might also look at our product We're alpha testing direct importing of HyperCard stacks we've even made the test release available for anonymous FTP so we're obviously the closest in MetaCard runs on most UNIX workstations and costs Email to for more Scott Thanks in advance Scott Raney Remember the better you look the more you'll see Lidia